text:
Spring is in full swing… Wild corvids  are actively searching for nesting materials. Mefisto is feeling quite romantic these days. 🖤✨

Soon, I’ll be busy helping many wild birds. Every year, I sponsor various crow protection programs. Unfortunately, in Japan, power company workers often destroy nests, even when they pose no threat to power lines. As a result, many chicks are left orphaned or even killed. 💔

Farmers also have a cruel habit of hanging crows upside down by their feet to scare others away from peanut and crop fields. This leads to a slow, painful death. Its illegal, but many people dont care. I personally drive around during the season, rescuing as many birds as I can. Thankfully, my cousin and her friends also help me in this mission. 🚗🖤

This enclosure, where Mefisto and my other birds usually have their meals, is mainly used for wild birds in spring. (I have six of them, each 2x2 meters.) Mefisto actually lives inside my house he just eats and bathes in this space. 🛁🐦

I hope that one day, Mefisto’s popularity will help people realize just how intelligent and fascinating ravens  truly are. 🖤✨
